To build the HPS binaries from a host computer, you'll have to use make to correctly specify and configure the toolchain;

CFLAGS="-Wall -O3 -pipe -fomit-frame-pointer -Wall -march=armv7-a -mtune=cortex-a9 -mfpu=neon" ./configure --prefix=/usr --host=arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf
make

On the internal PV dev machines, you may also use;

sh autogen.sh

CXX="/usr/x-tools/x-tools7h/arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf/bin/arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf-g++" \
CC="/usr/x-tools/x-tools7h/arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf/bin/arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf-gcc" \
CFLAGS="-Wall -O3 -pipe -fomit-frame-pointer -Wall -march=armv7-a -mtune=cortex-a9 -mfpu=neon" \
CPPFLAGS="-Wall -O3 -pipe -fomit-frame-pointer -Wall -march=armv7-a -mtune=cortex-a9 -mfpu=neon" \
CXXFLAGS="-Wall -O3 -pipe -fomit-frame-pointer -Wall -march=armv7-a -mtune=cortex-a9 -mfpu=neon" \
./configure --prefix=/usr --host=arm-unknown-linux-gnueabihf

make

To build for either Tate (Cyan) or Vaunt (Crimson), you may specify the option as CFLAG in
configure.ac. Legal values are either -DVAUNT or -DTATE
